  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nOfficial docker images are already provided for geth [here](https://hub.docker.com/r/ethereum/client-go/), but only support amd64 arch. Considering there is the use case of running geth inside a docker container and that different architectures are becoming increasingly popular (arm specifically) providing images for other architectures makes sense.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nThis could be implemented in one of two ways:\r\n\r\n1. Like in the [Dockerfile](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/Dockerfile) by downloading and compiling geth inside a builder container;\r\n2. Simply downloading and installing the precompiled binaries for each release.\r\n\r\nDocker Inc has a [guide](https://www.docker.com/blog/multi-arch-images/) on building multi-arch images.\r\n\r\nI am willing to implement this feature, but need guidance on the current build process.",
