    "body": "We are using docker hub automated builds, which does not support building ARM at the moment. We do not want to maintain a new build infra for making specialized images. The Dockerfile supplied by Geth will build fine on arm (and I'm guessing other systems too), so if you want to run non-amd64, you'll need to build the image yourself for now.\r\n\r\nI don't think Docker Hub will introduce non-amd64 builds any time soon, so I don't think we'll add it soon either. Maybe if there's some very very good reason in the future to maintain a custom builder we might consider it, but currently we see no advantage.",
